Class HtmlAttributes

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.rendersnake.HtmlAttributes
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    CharactersWriteable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    JQueryAttributes

    public class HtmlAttributes
extends Object
implements CharactersWriteable
    HtmlAttributes captures a set of attribute key and values. Instances have a write-once-only behavior; values can not be read or changed. The result is available using asCharSequence()
    Author:
    e.micklei

      • RENDER_DATA_TEST_ATTRIBUTE

        public static boolean RENDER_DATA_TEST_ATTRIBUTE
        This class field controls whether the data-test attribute will be written when dataTest("...") is called. It can be used by Web testing tools that need element identification where the id is missing. On default, it is rendered (true).
